Nicklaus 2025-08-24 11:06 a.m.
MINUTE ORDER: UPON CONSIDERATION of Plaintiffs Motion for Temporary Restraining Order, the Court, finding that swift, decisive action is essential to preserve the status quo, see, e.g., Granny Goose Foods, Inc. v. Brotherhood of Teamsters, 415 U.S. 423, 439 (1974), and upon weighing the four factorsnamely, the (1) likelihood of success on the merits, (2) irreparable harm in the absence of relief, (3) balance of equities, and (4) public interestset forth in Winter v. Natural Res. Def. Council, Inc., 555 U.S. 7, 20 (2008), and upon concluding, at least at this stage, that such factors favor interim relief, it is ORDERED that Defendant, including his officers, agents, servants, contractors, and persons acting at his direction or in participation with him be, and they hereby are, forthwith ENJOINED from advertising, offering, selling, or otherwise attempting to sell the Medford Home, as described in the Complaint, to any third party; and further ENJOINED from transferring or dissipating funds received from Plaintiff in exchange for the Medford Home, unless Defendant shall post a surety bond in the amount of $900,000.00; and IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that this Temporary Restraining Order shall be in effect for 14 days, or until such further order of the Court.

/s/ Nicklaus_s
